 "awd_abstract_narration": "For almost thirty years, control by eigenvalue-eigenvector assignment           and quadratic optimization (including LQR, LQG, LQR-LTR) have been the          most popular controller design methods for multi-input, multi-output            systems.  However, these methods can only guarantee that the control            system state vector as a whole behaves well.  Very little is said               about the transient behavior of individual state variables.  This               proposal introduces the idea of Covariance Control, which is a method           for ensuring a \"good behavior\" of each state variable separately.  We           believe that covariance control can become more powerful and useful             than the more popular state-space control methods.",
